replies.bodyText:
As you say "future", I understand that this pull request remains "as is" for the merge, right?
This is something I thought about, but to be honest I wan't sure about the expected implementation. As the buildTicketExpirationPolicy method does not accept any parameter, I couldn't think of any solution except than creating every time an expiration policy builder from the service PGT policy. Something like:
if (servicePgtPolicy != null) {
  LOGGER.trace("Overriding proxy-granting ticket policy with the specific policy: [{}]", servicePgtPolicy);
  val servicePGTExpirationPolicyBuilder =
new RegisteredServicePGTExpirationPolicyBuilder(servicePgtPolicy);
  return serviceTicket.grantProxyGrantingTicket(pgtId, authentication, 
servicePGTExpirationPolicyBuilder.buildTicketExpirationPolicy());
Is this what you had in mind?
